text: Tine Rustad Albertsen (née Kristiansen, born 12 February 1980) is a Norwegian handball player, who previously played for Larvik HK. She made her debut on the Norwegian national team in 2005, and played 43 matches and scored 52 goals. "Landslagsprofiler - Tine Rustad Kristiansen" - Norges Håndballforbund (www.handball.no) (Retrieved on 5 December 2008) Former club is Fjellhammer IL (Norway). She won the Women's EHF Cup Winners' Cup with the club Larvik HK in 2004/2005, and in 2007/2008. ==References== Category:1980 births Category:Living people Category:Norwegian female handball players Category:People from Lørenskog
